== Notable alumni ==

*[[Kim Glass]] is an American indoor [[volleyball]] player who joined the [[U.S. national team]] in the [[Olympics]] and won a silver medal in the 2008 [[Beijing Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arizonawildcats.com/sports/w-volley/mtt/glass_kim00.html|title=Kim Glass Profile|publisher=University of Arizona}}</ref>
*[[Jonathan Groff]] is a singer and stage, television, and [[film actor]] who worked in the musical [[Spring Awakening]] and the television series [[Glee (TV series)|Glee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jonathangroff.org/index.php?/rokstories/fp-rokstories/jonathan-groff-biography.html|title=Jonathan Groff Biography|publisher=Jonathangroff.org}}</ref>
*[[Floyd Landis]] is a professional [[Road bicycle racer|cyclist]] who won several events including the [[Tour of California 2006|Tour of California in 2006]], and the [[Tour de France 2006|Tour de France in 2006]] of which he was convicted of a doping case.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topendsports.com/sport/cycling/profiles/landis-floyd.htm|title=Floyd Landis|publisher=Topend Sports Network}}</ref>
*[[Kevin Shaffer]] is an [[Right tackle|American football offensive tackle]] who played for the [[Atlanta Falcons]], [[Cleveland Browns]], and [[Chicago Bears]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/player/kevinshaffer/2505001/profile|title=Kevin Shaffer|publisher=NFL}}</ref>
*[[Ryan G. Manelick]] was an American [[defense contractor]] who worked in [[Baghdad, Iraq]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observertoday.com/page/content.detail/id/24005/Ryan-Manelick-.html|title=Ryan Manelick|publisher=The Observer}}</ref>

